    <h3>The art of German motorclass has a unique architecture in three major companies. Many of these companies came out of the second world war and assisted in the economical rebirth of Germany. The Notable Karl Benz developed the four-stroke internal combustion engine in 1887. This invention marked the beginning of the classical art of automobiles </h3>
